Hey,

Related Babel issue: https://github.com/babel/babel/issues/9465

Basically, async private methods get transpiled wrongly by Babel, resulting in something that looks like this:

```js
class SomeClass_SomeClass extends react_default.a.Component {
  constructor() {
    super(...arguments);

    _defineProperty(this, "state", getInitialState(this.props));

    _defineProperty(this, "someFunction", async (props, state) => {
      ...
    }
  }
}
```

Safari 10.3.1 doesn't seem to like it, throwing this error:
`Can't find private variable @derivedConstructor` on the `async` keyword.

I'm not sure how compat-table is used by Babel, but please tell me if I can help solving this!

Thanks in advance
